@ThinkingandTinkering Yeah, he may have a bit much 'flair' for my tastes, but his mechanical aptitude is inspiring. If I catch one of his next videos early enough I'll pitch the idea of using swappable, mechanical rubber batteries to power his auto-repeaters. 
I'm picturing two parallel geared axles of very different axle diameters, and identical(could also be different) gear diameters, with one gear between them so they rotate the same direction. A long rubber strip which was previously affixed at one end to and wound around the small axle, would then have its free end affixed to the wide axle. Rotating the axles would then wind the strip onto the wide axle while simultaneously stretching the it a set amount at every point, and storing the energy in the stretched state which could then be returned instantly, and presumably with a constant output power.
I think that would work. At least, it does in my mental model.
